# Button

An interactive control that triggers an action, submits a form, or resets it.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button([], [html.text("Primary")]),
    button.button([button.icon_only(), attribute.aria_label("Next")], [
      icon.arrow_right([]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add button
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([], [html.text("Click me")])
}
```

## Variants

Six visual styles to cover anything from primary CTAs to ghost-style toolbar controls.

### Primary

The standard high-contrast variant for primary page actions.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([], [html.text("Primary Button")])
}
```

### Secondary

Lower-emphasis filled button for supporting actions that sit beside a primary.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([button.secondary()], [html.text("Secondary Button")])
}
```

### Accent

Brand-aligned button for feature actions and high-visibility CTAs.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([button.accent()], [html.text("Accent Button")])
}
```

### Outline

Bordered, transparent button for low-emphasis actions that still need a visible affordance.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([button.outline()], [html.text("Outline Button")])
}
```

### Ghost

Borderless, transparent button for the lowest-emphasis actions and toolbar controls.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([button.ghost()], [html.text("Ghost Button")])
}
```

### Destructive

Filled button for irreversible or dangerous actions like delete, remove, or revoke.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([button.destructive()], [html.text("Destructive Button")])
}
```

## Examples

Adjust the size, state, or layout of a button with modifier attributes.

### Inline Icon

Include leading or trailing icons in your buttons using the inline slots.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button([button.ghost(), button.xs()], [
      icon.plus([button.icon_start()]),
      html.text("Create New"),
    ]),
    button.button([button.secondary(), button.sm()], [
      icon.copy([button.icon_start()]),
      html.text("Copy"),
    ]),
    button.button([], [
      html.text("Download"),
      icon.download([button.icon_end()]),
    ]),
    button.button([button.destructive(), button.lg()], [
      icon.trash([button.icon_start()]),
      html.text("Delete Record"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Icon Only

Render a square button sized for a single icon child using the icon only attribute.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import ui/button
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button(
      [button.icon_only(), button.xs(), attribute.aria_label("Next")],
      [icon.arrow_right([])],
    ),
    button.button(
      [
        button.secondary(),
        button.icon_only(),
        button.sm(),
        attribute.aria_label("Change layout"),
      ],
      [icon.layout_template([])],
    ),
    button.button(
      [button.outline(), button.icon_only(), attribute.aria_label("Close")],
      [icon.x([])],
    ),
    button.button(
      [
        button.destructive(),
        button.icon_only(),
        button.lg(),
        attribute.aria_label("Delete"),
      ],
      [icon.trash([])],
    ),
  ])
}
```

### Sizes

Scale a button from extra small to large using the various size attributes.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button([button.xs()], [html.text("Extra Small")]),
    button.button([button.sm()], [html.text("Small")]),
    button.button([], [html.text("Medium")]),
    button.button([button.lg()], [html.text("Large")]),
  ])
}
```

### Disabled

Block interactivity and reduce opacity using the disabled attribute.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button([attribute.disabled(True)], [html.text("Primary")]),
    button.button([button.ghost(), attribute.disabled(True)], [
      html.text("Ghost"),
    ]),
    button.button([button.destructive(), attribute.disabled(True)], [
      html.text("Destructive"),
    ]),
    button.button(
      [
        attribute.disabled(True),
        button.icon_only(),
        attribute.aria_label("Next"),
      ],
      [icon.arrow_right([])],
    ),
  ])
}
```

### Pending

Mark a button as busy by setting aria-busy, revealing a spinner child if present. Pair with disabled.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/icon
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button(
      [
        button.secondary(),
        attribute.aria_busy(True),
        attribute.disabled(True),
        button.xs(),
      ],
      [spinner.icon([]), html.text("Secondary")],
    ),
    button.button(
      [
        button.outline(),
        attribute.aria_busy(True),
        attribute.disabled(True),
        button.sm(),
      ],
      [spinner.icon([]), html.text("Outline")],
    ),
    button.button(
      [
        button.destructive(),
        attribute.aria_busy(True),
        attribute.disabled(True),
      ],
      [
        spinner.icon([]),
        html.text("Destructive"),
      ],
    ),
    button.button(
      [
        attribute.aria_busy(True),
        attribute.disabled(True),
        button.icon_only(),
        button.lg(),
        attribute.aria_label("Next"),
      ],
      [spinner.icon([]), icon.arrow_right([])],
    ),
  ])
}
```

### Invalid

Surface an error ring when a button is the visible trigger for an invalid form control by setting aria-invalid.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.button([attribute.aria_invalid("true")], [html.text("Primary")]),
    button.button([button.outline(), attribute.aria_invalid("true")], [
      html.text("Outline"),
    ]),
    button.button([button.ghost(), attribute.aria_invalid("true")], [
      html.text("Ghost"),
    ]),
    button.button([button.destructive(), attribute.aria_invalid("true")], [
      html.text("Destructive"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Full Width

Use the full width attribute to stretch a button to fill its parent's width.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([attribute.class("max-w-sm"), button.full_width()], [
    html.text("Full Width"),
  ])
}
```

## As a Link

Render an anchor styled as a button for navigation rather than actions.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    button.link([attribute.href("/get-started")], [html.text("Get Started")]),
    button.link([button.outline(), attribute.href("/docs")], [
      html.text("View Docs"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Constructors

Four constructors, each one produces a different button behavior.

| Constructor | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `button.button(attrs, children)` | Runs an action without submitting a form; renders type="button". |
| `button.submit(attrs, children)` | Submits its enclosing form; renders type="submit". |
| `button.reset(attrs, children)` | Resets its enclosing form's fields; renders type="reset". |
| `button.link(attrs, children)` | An anchor styled as a button, for navigation rather than actions. |

### Variants

Sets the button's visual emphasis and intent.

| Variant | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `button.primary()` | The default high-contrast fill for the primary action, usually one per page or form. |
| `button.secondary()` | Lower-emphasis fill for supporting actions beside a primary. |
| `button.accent()` | Brand-aligned fill for feature actions and high-visibility CTAs. |
| `button.outline()` | Bordered and transparent, for low-emphasis actions that still need a visible affordance. |
| `button.ghost()` | Borderless and transparent, for the lowest-emphasis actions and toolbar controls. |
| `button.destructive()` | Filled, for irreversible or dangerous actions like delete or revoke. |

### Size Attributes

Adjusts the button's height, padding, and font size.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `button.xs()` | Extra-small, for dense toolbars and inline controls. |
| `button.sm()` | Small, a common choice for compact forms. |
| `button.md()` | Medium, the default; matches a button with no size attribute. |
| `button.lg()` | Large, for hero CTAs. |

### Layout Attributes

Changes the button's shape or width within its container.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `button.icon_only()` | Renders a square button sized for a single icon child. |
| `button.full_width()` | Stretches the button to fill its parent's width. |

### State Attributes

Signals the button's availability and any in-flight or error state.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `attribute.disabled(True)` | Blocks pointer events, reduces opacity, and removes the button from the tab order. |
| `attribute.aria_disabled(True)` | Same visual treatment as disabled but keeps the button focusable so screen readers can still announce it. Suited to toolbars and async actions. |
| `attribute.aria_busy(True)` | Centers a spinner child over the content, if passed. Pair with disabled to block interaction. |
| `attribute.aria_invalid("true")` | Adds a destructive error ring when the button is the visible trigger for an invalid form control. |

### Icon Slot Attributes

Apply these to the **icon child element**, not the button itself.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `button.icon_start()` | Marks an icon as the leading (inline-start) child. The button reduces its leading padding. |
| `button.icon_end()` | Marks an icon as the trailing (inline-end) child. The button reduces its trailing padding. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the button's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="button"]` | The button or link element. |
| `[data-variant="primary\|secondary\|..."]` | The element, tagged with its active variant. |
| `[data-size="xs\|sm\|md\|lg"]` | The element, tagged with its active size. |
| `[data-full-width="true"]` | A button stretched to fill its container. |
| `[data-icon-only="true"]` | A square button sized for a single icon child. |
| `[aria-busy="true"]` | A pending button. |
| `[disabled]` | A disabled button, dropped from the tab order. |
| `[aria-disabled="true"]` | An inactive button, kept focusable. |
| `[aria-invalid="true"]` | A button flagged as an invalid form trigger. |
| `[data-icon="inline-start\|inline-end"]` | A leading or trailing icon child. |
| `[data-slot="spinner"]` | The spinner child centered over a pending button's label. |

## Accessibility

**Native button semantics.** Renders as a native `<button>` (or an `<a>` when built with `button.link`), so activation, focus, and the disabled state come from the browser. Setting aria-busy="true" on a pending button means assistive tech announces the busy state. Icon-only buttons have no text content, so give each one an accessible name with aria-label.

### Keyboard

| Key | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Tab | Move focus to the button. |
| Shift + Tab | Move focus back to the previous focusable element. |
| Enter | Activate the button, or follow the link when built with button.link. |
| Space | Activate the button. Anchors built with button.link do not respond to Space. |

